main event: An observation of a bright white object flying south over Cedar Key, Florida in April 1956.
interesting points: The object was observed for two minutes,The object was described as being the size of a dime held at arm's length,The sighting occurred at an angle of approximately 20 degrees before the object disappeared over the horizon,The report suggests that the sighting might have been an aircraft due to high air traffic in the area,The observation was categorized as a ground-visual type.
